36
3524:05:10,933.3330001831055 --> 3644:25:10,933.3330001831055
The Tang Monk gasped. "Oh no!"

37
3644:26:50,933.3330001831055 --> 3766:50:10,933.3330001831055
Bajie stared in horror at the torn scroll.

38
3766:51:50,933.3330001831055 --> 3889:30:10,933.3330001831055
Wukong smiled. "Don't worry, Master."

39
3889:31:50,933.3330001831055 --> 4004:18:30,933.3330001831055
The monkey gently picked the rest of the scroll off the rock.

40
4004:20:10,933.3330001831055 --> 4068:00:10,933.3330001831055
"The scroll is fine."

41
4068:01:50,933.3330001831055 --> 4151:03:30,933.3330001831055
"But it's ripped!" cried the monk.

42
4151:05:10,933.3330001831055 --> 4253:08:30,933.3330001831055
Bajie hung his head.

43
4253:10:10,933.3330001831055 --> 4320:41:50,933.3330001831055
[g@"Tell me something, Master," said Wukong.

44
4320:43:30,933.3330001831055 --> 4391:45:10,933.3330001831055
"Are you perfect?"@g]

45
4391:46:50,933.3330001831055 --> 4487:00:10,933.3330001831055
[g@The monk gave Wukong a confused look.

46
4487:01:50,933.3330001831055 --> 4542:16:50,933.3330001831055
"Of course not."@g]

47
4542:18:30,933.3330001831055 --> 4641:25:10,933.3330001831055
"Am I perfect?" asked the monkey.

48
4641:26:50,933.3330001831055 --> 4756:33:30,933.3330001831055
The Tang Monk shook his head.

49
4756:35:10,933.3330001831055 --> 4865:25:10,933.3330001831055
[g@"How about Bajie?" Wukong smirked.

50
4865:26:50,933.3330001831055 --> 4965:05:10,933.3330001831055
"We all know he's not perfect."@g]

51
4965:06:50,933.3330001831055 --> 5039:55:10,933.3330001831055
The pig snorted.

52
5039:56:50,933.3330001831055 --> 5148:38:30,933.3330001831055
"Nothing on Earth or in Heaven is perfect," said Wukong.

53
5148:40:10,933.3330001831055 --> 5248:55:10,933.3330001831055
"So why should the True Scriptures be any different?

54
5248:56:50,933.3330001831055 --> 5363:25:10,933.3330001831055
